cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT, cs.HC, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision problems related to eye images, such as shape registration and gaze estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses computer graphics techniques to build eye-region models, which suggests a possible fit with cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of realistic illumination and shape variations in eye-region training data, which could relate to cs.GT (Computer Graphics and Computer-Aided Design). The paper also mentions the potential applications of their method in human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper evaluates their method's performance on cross-dataset appearance-based gaze estimation, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
